# 2. Write a Python program to convert Celsius to Fahrenheit?

""" In this program we take input from user and convert from Celsius
    to Fahrenheit by using formula (1°C × 9/5) + 32 = 33.8°F.   """

cel = input("Enter the temperature in Celsius: ")
ft = (float(cel) * 9/5) +32
print("For {0} Degree Celsius the Temperature in Fahrenheit is {1}0F." .format(cel,ft))
